Class Node

    public class Node
extends EditableNode
implements INode
    The object which represents all digital assets.

    Nodes

    Overview

    All digital assets in Amazon Cloud Drive are represented as Nodes. Nodes can be folders, images, videos, and other content. Nodes always have metadata and sometimes have binary data associated with them. Nodes have an id field which are used to identify them.

    Folder Nodes

    Folders are a kind of Node that have a parent-child relationship with other Nodes.

    Content Nodes

    Content Nodes have properties that are specific to their type of content. For example, an image node has properties like the model of the camera that was used to capture the image.

    Trash

    Nodes can be sent to the trash when the customer no longer wants them. The trash is a special kind of node that is similar to the folder. Its children are the Nodes which are trashed.
